It&#8217;s understood flight 441 was heading from Houston to Frankfurt when a threat was called into the airline's corporate headquarters. JOHANNESBURG Aviation authorities say a Lufthansa flight has been diverted to New York s John F. Kennedy international airport due to a bomb threat.It s understood flight 441 was heading from Houston to Frankfurt on Monday night, when a threat was called into the airline's corporate headquarters. The pilot was notified and chose to divert to JFK as a precaution. The plane was taken to a remote area of the airport where all 530 passengers and crew were evacuated.